            html: `<p><a title="Lesson 17: Connecting Particle ~고 and ~고 싶다 &ldquo;I want to&rdquo;" href="https://www.howtostudykorean.com/?page_id=1255">Lesson 17:</a>&nbsp;In this lesson, you will be introduced to your first (of very many) connecting particles in Korean. You can usually use these particles to separate two two ideas/phrases/sentences. In this lesson you will learn about 고 and how it can be used in sentences, also using the example of ~고 싶다. You will also learn that some words (usually position-like words) play by different rules than most verbs in these situations.</p>`,
